(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on comparing when to use a stack versus a queue.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in lists, stacks, queues, trees, and choosing the right) Tj
T*
(structure that the question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Data Structures step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on structure identification and use cases.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid using a structure without understanding its behavior while) Tj
T*
(solving it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
